node.title: NT COVID-19 hospital patient numbers leap to a new record of 105
node.alt: A grey sphere with red and orange blotches.
node.description: There are now 105 people with COVID-19 in hospital in the Northern Territory, up from 95 Thursday, with three people in intensive care.
node.content: ["The number of coronavirus patients in Northern Territory hospitals has\u00a0grown\u00a0by 10 to a new record of 105, NT Chief Minister Michael Gunner has said.\u00a0", "Patients in hospital\u00a0represent about 2.5 per cent of the NT's total active cases.", "Fourteen patients require\u00a0oxygen and three are receiving care in the intensive care unit.", "A total of\u00a0940 new COVID-19 cases were recorded across the Territory in the 24 hours to 8pm last night.", "The case numbers released yesterday have been revised up from 626 to 747.", "There are now 4,200 active coronavirus cases in the NT, Mr Gunner\u00a0said.", "More than half are in Darwin and Palmerston.", "From 2pm today, the community of Ampilatwatja in Central Australia will enter a 48-hour lockdown after several cases were recorded there, Mr Gunner said.", "He said the community had\u00a0a very low vaccination rate.", "More to come.\u00a0"]
